-- Harper Announces C$250 Million Fund for Canada Auto Resea
-- B y   H u g o   M i l l e r
-- 2013-01-04T16:43:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-04/harper-announces-c-250-million-fund-for-canada-auto-resea.html
Prime Minister  Stephen Harper  said
the federal government will spend C$250 million ($254 million)
over five years to support research and development by
automakers based in  Canada .  Harper said in a news release handed to reporters that the
funding will be used to extend the Automotive Innovation Fund
until 2018.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hugo Miller in Toronto at 
